PAYSOFF TINKOFF v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 5471. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. April 25, 1935. Laurence M. Fine, of Chicago, Ill., for appellant. Dwight H. Green, of Chicago, Ill., for the United States.

Before EVANS and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellee, it is now here ordered and adjudged by this court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed.
